--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TARBALL CONTENTS:

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

-homework_4.pdf: Type set explanation of my solution to the problems


-src: Folder housing the source code for any executables in the assignment.

	-makefile
	
	- odeint_solver.cpp: source code for problem 1a
	- leapfrog.cpp: source code for problem 1b
	- verlet.cpp: source code for problem 1c
	
	- ODEINT suite: associated *.h and *.cpp files


-outputs: Folder containing my versions of the textfiles generated by my
	  algorithms. Due to budget cuts, running any of the above programs
	  WILL NOT save files in this folder (they'll appear in /src)


-plots.ipynb: Jupyter notebook used to read-in and plot outputs of the 
	     executables
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTRUCTIONS:

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To compile the code, simply input "make" into the terminal while in the source directory.

The makefile will generate three  executables: 'odeint_solver','leapfrog'' and 'verlet'. 
Running any of the executables will prompt the user for initial conditions.

The three executables will each generate textfiles. The output files I used to make any plots
featured in the writeup can be found in the in the 'output' directory.

The plot heavy nature of this assignment means that the Python code comes in the form of a Jupyter 
notebook this time around.

